<br>
Thomal, it is the best post I have seen from ya bro. But I think I need clarification on one thing. Did you get decieved by IF or by TSO? Which do you feel you were taken advantage of? <br>
<br>
Yes, after reading the whole thread, I did feel somewhat better knowing that for ONCE in the game, Conquest feels we got them a little. I dont know if you know how it feels to work on a mob for 6+ hours and then to lose it. This isnt written to get sympathy or feelings and if you want to belittle me for it fine, but it sure hurts when it has happened. I dont care for the way your guild hurts people in this game and I will NOT be threatened by you or them. It makes me very angry and if you want to flame it out, I will. Otherwise, have some regards for others and there feelings. Sure Conquest wants the mobs but are they worth the HURT your guild causes to others? Is it not obvious to you that by overrunning a guild to get to a mob will have some effect on that guild? Or do you simply not care as a powergamer what others think of you. Sure its easy to that the &quot;quake&quot; attitude and say its a silly mob and not even real. But what you are missing is that is real is EFFORT, TEAMWORK, COMMUNICATION, ETC that goes along with attempting to defeat some of the mobs that Conquest/IF attempt. These are not easy, die in a sec mobs. There are 20 minute battles with chain rezing going on to kill some of them. I died 17 times trying to figure out how to kill CT one night, I will be darned if I didnt develop some feelings that night about attempting him and wanting to try him again and not lose (and we did WHOOT). <br>
<br>
I dont see how some of you guys can be walk around seeing so little of what you do. Esp you Thomal, we have talking in RL about this some and you know the way I feel, might makes right, I respect that, but not at hurting others. I wished that Conquest, under Itz, was going to work with IF more than compete with it. And I was auctually quite surprised to here Itz and Deavi speaking to each other again. But that was a while back and I guess we have crossed paths once more. To bad. For both of our guilds.  <p><p align="center"><img src="http://www.world-net.net/users/twoslow/kaisen1.jpg">
